---
title: Edamame & Mandarin Orange Crunch Salad with Spicy Sesame-Peanut Dressing
description: Summer called, it wants you to know it’s time to get ready for some well-deserved fun in the sun! This hearty, vibrant lunch idea is packed with delicious veggie—baby lettuce, red cabbage, and carrots form a crisp base for supremely satisfying salad. You’ll add protein-packed edamame, juicy mandarin orange segments, nutty sesame seeds, and fresh scallion greens for color, texture, and crunch. It’s all tossed with a slightly sweet and very savory peanut-sesame dressing that’s frankly the star of the show. Summer glow, here we come!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/edamame-mandarin-orange-crunch-salad-79cbbf0f.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/edamame-mandarin-orange-crunch-salad-643ee0774a156de37a08400c-0f3cd18a.pdf
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 460 kcal
  fat: 29 g
  saturated fat: 4.5 g
  carbohydrates: 38 g
  sugar: 22 g
  protein: 14 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 720 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/edamame-and-mandarin-orange-crunch-salad-643ee0774a156de37a08400c
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 10 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce.

Place @edamame{4%ounce} in a small #microwave-safe bowl{} and microwave until warm and slightly tender, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; chop leaves into bite-size pieces. Thinly slice @scallions{2}(thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Peel and separate @mandarin orange{1} into segments; halve each segment crosswise.

In a large #bowl{}, whisk together @peanut butter{1.15%ounce}, @sesame dressing{3%ounce}, and as many @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} as you like. (TIP: Knead peanut butter packet before opening to make whisking easier.) Add water 1 tsp at a time until dressing reaches a drizzling consistency.

Add lettuce, @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce}, @shredded carrots{4%ounce}, scallion whites, and three-quarters of the mandarin pieces; toss to coat. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide salad between bowls. Top with edamame, @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}, scallion greens, and remaining mandarin pieces. Serve.